  • Module streamio
  • Module string

  • Module ttyutil - A utility library for terminal-based input and output
  • Module udc - User-defined channels
  • Module useful - General utilities
  • Module video - V4L(2) frame-grabber interface

    • Tag reset.all - Reset all components to default state

  • Protocol G3D.GEN.CONTROL - Polygon points generator control
    • Tag add.scale - Add to the current scale
    • Tag add.trans - Add to the current translation
    • Tag relink - Reconnect I/O channels
    • Tag reset - Reset generator to default state
    • Tag set.scale - Absolutely set the scale
    • Tag set.trans - Absolutely set the translation
  • Constant G3D.MAX.POLY.POINTS - Maximum number of points in a polygon (see )
  • Constant G3D.MAX.SCAN.HEIGHT - Maximum height of any particular polygon
  • Protocol G3D.PGN.CONTROL - Polygon generator control
    • Tag reset - Reset polygon generator to default state
    • Tag set.backfaces - Whether back faces of solid objects should be generated
    • Tag set.face.colour - Set individual face colour
    • Tag set.face.colours - Set all face colours
    • Tag set.polyid - Set polygon ID (0-255)
    • Tag set.trimap - Generate triangular polygons only
  • Record G3D.POINT2 - Integer point in 2D space
  • Record G3D.POINT2.3 - Integer point in 2D space, original Z multiplied up
  • Record G3D.POINT3 - Real point in 3D space (REAL32s)
  • Record G3D.POLY - General polygon in 2D space, orignal Z multiplied up
  • Record G3D.POLY.SCAN - Scan-line converted polygon in 2D space
  • Protocol G3D.PRJ.CONTROL - Polygon points 3D-to-2D projection control
    • Tag reset - Reset projector to default state
    • Tag set.2dshift - Set 2D translation
    • Tag set.3dshift - Set 3D translation (applied before projection)
    • Tag set.scaling - Set 2D scaling
    • Tag set.zdepth - Set Z depth offset (pushes scene away from camera)
  • Protocol G3D.PSC.CONTROL - Polygon scan-line generator control
    • Tag reset - Resets scan-line generator to default state
    • Tag set.zcolour - Whether the pixel colour used is adjusted for Z depth
  • Protocol G3D.RDR.CONTROL - Polygon render (shader) control
    • Tag reset - Resets shader to default state
    • Tag set.mode - Set shader mode (see )
  • Protocol G3D.RENDER.ENGINE.LINK - Graphics pipeline link protocol
    • Tag raster - Raster to render on and forward
    • Tag set.next - Set the next renderer in the pipeline
  • Group G3D.RENDER.MODE - polygon rendering modes
    • Constant G3D.RENDER.MODE.GLENZ - Glenz-effect shading
    • Constant G3D.RENDER.MODE.NONE - Constant shading
    • Constant G3D.RENDER.MODE.NORM - Normal vector based shading
  • Protocol G3D.ROT.CONTROL - Points rotation control
    • Tag add.increment - Add to the increment
    • Tag reset - Reset rotation to default state
    • Tag set.angle - Absolutely set the angle of rotation
    • Tag set.increment - Absolutely set the increment
    • Tag set.mode - Set the rotation mode (see )
  • Group G3D.ROTATE.MODE - point/polygon rotation modes
    • Constant G3D.ROTATE.MODE.DEMO - Demo-effect rotations
    • Constant G3D.ROTATE.MODE.NONE - No rotation
    • Constant G3D.ROTATE.MODE.NX - Negative rotate on X axis
    • Constant G3D.ROTATE.MODE.NY - Negative rotate on Y axis
    • Constant G3D.ROTATE.MODE.NZ - Negative rotate on Z axis
    • Constant G3D.ROTATE.MODE.X - Rotate on X axis
    • Constant G3D.ROTATE.MODE.Y - Rotate on Y axis
    • Constant G3D.ROTATE.MODE.Z - Rotate on Z axis
  • Group G3D.SCENE.RO - Scene rotation ordering
    • Constant G3D.SCENE.RO.NONE - No rotations applied
    • Constant G3D.SCENE.RO.X - Rotate on X axis only
    • Constant G3D.SCENE.RO.XY - Rotate on X then Y
    • Constant G3D.SCENE.RO.XYZ - Rotate on X then Y then Z

    • Constant G3D.SCENE.RO.ZXY - Rotate on Z then X then Y
    • Constant G3D.SCENE.RO.ZY - Rotate on Z then Y
    • Constant G3D.SCENE.RO.ZYX - Rotate on Z then Y then X
  • Protocol G3D.SCENE.TRANS.LINK - Scene rotate pipeline link protocol
    • Tag reset - Reset to default settings
    • Tag set.next - Set the next scene transformer in a pipeline
    • Tag set.post.3dshift - Set 3D shift (after rotation, determines camera position)
    • Tag set.pre.3dshift - Set 3D shift (before rotation, determines centre of scene)
    • Tag set.rot.angles - Set rotations in X, Y and Z planes
    • Tag set.rot.diffs - Set differences for continuous rotation
    • Tag set.rot.order - Set rotation order (see )
    • Tag set.xyscale - Set X-Y scaling (lens angle)
  • Protocol G3D.SCL.CONTROL - Points scaler control
    • Tag reset - Reset scale to default state (1, 1, 1)
    • Tag set.3dscale - Set 3D scaling
  • Protocol G3D.TMR.CONTROL - Graphics pipeline speed control
    • Tag faster - Go faster
    • Tag pause - Pause/unpause the rasters flowing through the network
    • Tag reset - Resets the timer control
    • Tag set.fps - Set frames-per-second absolutely
    • Tag slower - Go slower
  • Protocol G3D.TRN.CONTROL - Points translation control
    • Tag reset - Reset translation to default state (0, 0, 0)
    • Tag set.3dshift - Set 3D translation
  • Channel type G3DC.PIECE.CTL - Used to control a particular piece
    • Variable gen.ctl? - Piece generator control
    • Variable in? - Piece control
    • Variable pgn.ctl? - Polygon convert control
    • Variable prj.ctl? - Projector control
    • Variable rdr.ctl? - Render control
  • Protocol G3DC.PIECE.CTL.IN - Chess piece control
    • Tag hide - Whether to make hidden
    • Tag move.pos - Move piece to specified position (animate!)
    • Tag set.pos - Set piece position on board (0-7,0-7)
  • Process GETAFF - Get the affinity of the current process
  • Protocol GETOPT - Responses from
    • Tag arg - A non-option argument (such as foo )
    • Tag bad - An unrecognised option
    • Tag done - No more options
    • Tag opt - An option (such as -a )
    • Tag opt.arg - An option with an argument (such as -a foo )
  • Protocol GETOPT.LONG - Responses from
    • Tag arg - A non-option argument (such as foo )
    • Tag bad - An unrecognised option
    • Tag done - No more options
    • Tag opt - An option (such as -a or --arg )
    • Tag opt.arg - An option with an argument (such as -a foo or --arg foo )

  • Channel type OCCADE - Channel bundle for communicating with Occade
  • Record OCCADE.COLLISION - Reports of collisions between sprites
    • Variable id - ID of the other sprite
    • Variable w, h - Width and height of the other sprite
    • Variable x, y - Position of the other sprite
  • Channel type OCCADE.INPUT - Channel bundle for carrying input events
    • Variable events! - Input events
    • Variable req? - Commands to the event filter
    • Variable resp! - Responses from the event filter
  • Protocol OCCADE.INPUT.REQ - Commands that can be sent to the event filter
    • Tag enable - Pick the types of events you're interested in
    • Tag quit - Close this event filter
  • Protocol OCCADE.INPUT.RESP - Responses from the event filter
  • Record OCCADE.PARAMS - Startup parameters for Occade
    • Variable depth - Pixel depth in bits
    • Variable width, height - Screen width and height in pixels
  • Channel type OCCADE.SPRITE - Channel bundle for controlling sprites
    • Variable collisions! - Reports of collisions with other sprites
    • Variable req? - Commands to the sprite
    • Variable resp! - Responses from the sprite
  • Protocol OCCADE.SPRITE.REQ - Commands that can be sent to the sprite
    • Tag collisions - Enable or disable collision reports
    • Tag get.position - Get the position of the sprite
    • Tag get.size - Get the size of the sprite
    • Tag load.image - Set the sprite's image from a file
    • Tag load.raster - Set the sprite's image from a raster
    • Tag load.text - Set the sprite's image by rendering text
    • Tag move - Set the sprite's position
    • Tag quit - Make the sprite exit
    • Tag visible - Show or hide the sprite
  • Protocol OCCADE.SPRITE.RESP - Responses from the sprite
    • Tag get.position - The position of the sprite
    • Tag get.size - The size of the sprite
    • Tag return.raster - Returning a used raster
  • Constant OCCADE.TRANSPARENT.COLOUR - The colour in images that is considered transparent when drawing
  • Group OPEN.MODE - Constants for
    • Constant O.APPEND - Position file pointer at EOF before each write
    • Constant O.ASYNC - Generate a signal when IO becomes possible
    • Constant O.CREAT - Create if not already present
    • Constant O.DIRECT - Don't cache data for this file
    • Constant O.DIRECTORY - Fail if not opening a directory
    • Constant O.EXCL - Fail if is given and the file already exists
    • Constant O.LARGEFILE - Allow the file to be larger than 2GB
    • Constant O.NDELAY - Synonym for
    • Constant O.NOCTTY - Don't become controlling terminal
    • Constant O.NOFOLLOW - Don't follow symbolic links when opening
    • Constant O.NONBLOCK - Make operations on this FD not block
    • Constant O.RDONLY - Open for reading
    • Constant O.RDWR - Open for reading and writing
    • Constant O.SYNC - Open for synchronous IO
    • Constant O.TRUNC - Truncate to zero length after opening
    • Constant O.WRONLY - Open for writing

    • Tag connect - Connect to specified joystick
    • Tag num.sticks - Report number of joysticks present
    • Tag query.stick - Query characteristics of a particular stick
    • Tag quit - Tell the server process to terminate
  • Protocol P.SDLJOY.OUT - Joystick server output protocol
    • Tag error - General error result
    • Tag joystick - Connection to joystick handler
    • Tag num.sticks - Number of sticks
    • Tag query - Query result
  • Protocol P.SDLJS.EVENT - Joystick event protocol
    • Tag change - Reporting change in joystick status
    • Tag quit - Joystick server process terminating
  • Protocol P.SDLJS.EVENT.IN - Joystick event input protocol
    • Tag force.event - Pretend a change happened and generate a new event
  • Protocol P.SDLJS.IN - Joystick input protocol
    • Tag disable - Disable joystick data capture
    • Tag enable - Enable joystick data capture, returns client channel-end
    • Tag query - Query joystick (number of axes and buttons)
  • Protocol P.SDLJS.OUT - Joystick output protocol
    • Tag event.chan - Channel-end on which events are received
    • Tag query - Number of axes and buttons
  • Protocol P.SDLJSCALIBRATE.IN - Joystick calibration input protocol
    • Tag calibrate - Start joystick calibration
  • Protocol P.SDLJSCALIBRATE.OUT - Joystick calibration output protocol
    • Tag done - Calibration complete
    • Tag message - Message to be reported to the user

    • Process get.char - Read a character from the file into ch, skipping comments
    • Process get.number - Read a decimal number terminated by a single whitespace character from the file into n, skipping any preceding whitespace
    • Function is.whitespace - Is a character whitespace, as defined by the PPM spec?
    • Process raw.char - Read a character from the file into ch

  • Process render.polyscans - Renders polygon scan-line data onto a raster
  • Process render.polyscans.trigger - Renders polygon scan-line data onto a raster, sends triggers back to generator process
  • Process resize.string - Resize a string, keeping its contents intact

  • Function rotate2 - Generate a transformation matrix that rotates a 2D point around the origin

  • Function same.string - Compare two strings for equality

  • Process screen.driver - Shared screen process
  • Process screen.interpret - Interpret an array of screen update commands
  • Function search.match - Search a string for the first occurrence of any one of a given number of characters

  • Function seconds - Convert seconds to timer ticks
  • Process selector.add - Register a file descriptor with a selector

  • Process selector.start - Start an IO selector
